e world have sought to reduce animal-vehicle collisions and minimize road-crossing risks for wildlife, including efforts undertaken at the famed fauna overpasses of Banff National Park, the Singapore Eco-Link, "tunnels of love" in the Australian Alps, and others. Along the way, he acquaints readers with concepts and research in road ecology, describing the field's origins and future directions. Engaging and accessible, A Clouded Leopard in the Middle of the Road brings to the foreground an often-overlooked facet of humanity's footprint on earth.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aAnimalsxEffect of roads on. 0aHabitat conservation. 0aRoadsxEnvironmental aspects. 0aWildlife crossings. 4aEcology. 4aNature Guides & Natural History. 7aNATURE / Ecology.2bisacsh  aroad ecology, roads and biodiversity, impact of roads on wildlife, environmental impact of roads, cougar town, wildlife bridges, 99 percent invisible.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertCornell University Press Complete eBook-Package 2022z978311075182608iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2022 Englishz978311099389908iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2022z9783110994810oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Medicine and Life Sciences 2022 Englishz978311099319608iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Medicine and Life Sciences 2022z9783110993134oZDB-23-DPM08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUIUC Life Sciences 2023 eBook packagez978311123611740uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9781501763724?locatt=mode:legacy40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781501763724423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781501763724/original  a978-3-11-075182-6  Cornell University Press Complete eBook-Pa